{"tid":2247906,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"NY Post: twitter好多員工極度反侵 解釋咗對侵侵一方既打壓行為","createTime":"2020-10-18T08:19:06.000Z","updateTime":"2020-10-18T08:55:00.000Z","uid":48083,"like":7,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":7,"replies":[{"pid":"5f89acd674c373b5895e92d0aafc295a8e536bd0","tid":2247906,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-18T08:19:06.000Z","msg":"&ldquo;GET HIM OUT,&rdquo; posted a senior site reliability engineer on Aug. 18. &ldquo;What a f&ndash;king baboon.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nOne manager with almost nine years on the job said he was quite keen to watch Biden &ldquo;crush [Trump] in the election&rdquo; and that he hoped the president would &ldquo;be utterly humiliated while also suffering greatly from #COVID19.&rdquo; In another post he fantasized about the president being put on a ventilator.<br />\n<br />\nHe calls Trump &ldquo;a f&ndash;king idiot&rdquo; and the voters who elected him &mdash; &ldquo;hysterically f&ndash;king stupid people.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nAt the same time the employee has been a consistent cheerleader of his company&rsquo;s efforts to rein in the president on the platform and curb the spread of &ldquo;misinformation.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I&rsquo;m really proud of how quickly we&rsquo;ve worked to make this possible for the US elections,&rdquo; he wrote.<br />\n<br />\nOthers publicly wish the president harm.<br />\n<br />\nOne Twitter engineering manager said Trump should &ldquo;die in a fire&rdquo; in a January 2017 tweet. A year later, he rang in the new year by saying &ldquo;Happy 2018! Donald Trump is dead!&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n⋯⋯A talent brand program manager cried after Trump was elected president and publicly vowed to oppose him.<br />\n<br />\nA global project manager with more than a decade on the job posted proudly that he was phone banking for Biden.<br />\n<br />\nA vice president in sales finance said supporting Biden alone was not enough, and urged colleagues to spread cash to Dems in competitive Senate races.<br />\n<br />\nSpreading lies about the Trump family is also not beneath Twitter&rsquo;s sentinels. A senior staff engineer inquired why the media wasn&rsquo;t looking into Melania Trump&rsquo;s &ldquo;possible stint as a sex worker.&rdquo; (The first lady denied this allegation and successfully sued over it.)<br />\n<br />\nTwitter&rsquo;s &ldquo;head of integrity&rdquo; Yoel Roth was infamously busted over a series of old tweets revealing him to be a die-hard Trump hater.<br />\n<br />\nIn his posts, Roth &mdash; who helped author the policy update used by the company to flag and label posts from President Trump &mdash; compared White House officials to Nazis and Trump to a &ldquo;racist tangerine.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://nypost.com/2020/10/17/twitter-employees-reveal-deep-hatred-for-trump/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2020%2F10%2F17%2Ftwitter-employees-reveal-deep-hatred-for-trump%2F&d=lXXpVpUBFe4etFVyslLGPbV8WQSydv6El4C3YWjT4Eg%3D&h=28735e7d\" target=\"_blank\">https://nypost.com/2020/10/17/twitter-employees-reveal-deep-hatred-for-trump/</a>"},{"pid":"458e5b22ada2f18fe72c7223316bb77c5cb7744d","tid":2247906,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-18T08:19:36.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><strong><span class=\"x-large\"><span class=\"red\">警告：TVB戰線超過六日少於1000人參與<img src=\"/assets/faces/cat/shaking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong><span class=\"gold\"><span class=\"x-large\">【TVB戰線懶人區】(最後更新17 Oct 2110)<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/itdog4.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">【抵制偽人】Chanel (16 Oct)</span><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/chanel/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fchanel%2F&d=lXXpVpUBFe4etFVyslLGPbV8WQSydv6El4C3YWjT4Eg%3D&h=1e55dba3\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/ch